    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>
         Samuel T. Betts Jr. (d. 1948) was a businessman in Skaneateles, New York.
         Betts was a long-time resident of Skaneateles and an active member of civic organizations 
         such as the Skaneateles Library Association,
         Skaneateles Rotary Club, and on the board of appeals for the Village of Skaneateles. He was on the board of
         trustees for the Skaneateles Savings Bank and founded the Skaneateles Stamp Company, his main business venture.
         </p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The 
        
        <emph render="bold">Samuel T. Betts Jr. Papers</emph> contains 
        
        correspondence, 
            
        
        financial material, and
        
        memorabilia.</p>
      <p>
        <emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph> consists of correspondence with family members and 
            various clients of Betts' printing and stamp company, Skaneateles Stamp Co.</p>
      <p>
        <emph render="bold">Financial material</emph> includes checks and bank statements from the National Bank
        and Trust Co. of Skaneateles and Betts' receipts, both personal and business.</p>
      <p>
        <emph render="bold">Memorabilia</emph> consists of photographs of unknown individuals who could possibly
            be Betts's family, numerous calling cards and membership cards, souvenir postcards, and so on. </p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>Correspondence is arranged alphabetically by name of correspondent, 
            and within each folder chronologically. Financial material and memorabilia are arranged alphabetically by title, type, or topic.</p>
    </arrangement>
